rComments:
The prof is a ghost and the only interaction you will have outside of the biweekly email, will be with the TAs who are absolutely BRUTAL. The TAs in this class will grade you outside of the given criteria established in the guidelines handed out by the prof and will remove marks without giving feedback as to why.

AVOID

With a bit of effort (which is to be expected for a university class), this course is very doable! I also had an awesome TA which definitely helped. Considering how many students are in the class, I think the prof did an awesome job. The readings were also quite interesting! It was a great way to tune-up my academic French:)
Incredible prof in my opinion. Had a class of 1000 students online and managed it super well. 10/10 would recommend. If you give it a bit of effort, its actually pretty interesting. I promise!!

I took french with this prof in asynchrone, the class was actually super easy if you put in a bit of effort into it. The quizzes can get a bit confusing when it seems more than one answer could be correct. The class consisted of a few quizzes on writing and grammar, and one major writing project we prepared throughout the semestre. She's very nice!
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Professeure Dumas est accessible hors classe et donne des explications concises. Les tests de lecture sont difficilement evalues. Les presentations PowerPoints sont extremement longues et la voix vocale fait seulement que lire; une tache qui prends 1h30 et aurais pu se faire en 30 minutes. Il faut etre autonome pour reussir cette classe asynchrone.
She expects you to know what to do on time, which is reasonable except for the fact that her Brightspace platform is terribly unorganized
Un cours so easy to pass mais la prof complique les choses , et sa correction est terrible , well pick another prof if you can.

C'était vraiment une chouette expérience, c'est difficile de rendre le français attrayant, mais elle essaie de toujours rajouter de l'humour dans ses cours. N'hésitez pas a rigoler avec elle, ca lui fait plaisir et ca rend la classe plus fun ;). Le cours était plutôt facile surtout si le français est votre langue maternelle.
Boring class.
The class is extremely easy. Cours mal organisé
Boring class and she doesnt try to make it any more interesting, honestly pick another prof if you can.
Her classes are a bit redundant if you're already good in french, so it does get boring. Although, she can be pretty funny and a little extra sometimes.

Had to take this class cause it is mandatory.. it's the only reason. It is easy to get good grades if you go to every DGD and pay attention sometime in class, although not really necessary. She's always talking about herself and makes the material really boring, sadly... Anyway. Won't take this teacher again if not needed!
Awesome teacher, explains grading criteria clearly and if you follow them you will easily succeed.

Easiest class ever. Showed up to first and last lecture only and passed with 90%. All she does is explain what you're going to do in the DGD and she posts the powerpoint online so honestly don't waste your time going to this class.

Boring lectures that hardly anyone attends. Tough grader. The discussion groups are much more important then the lectures; they normally go over what she's said. Her power points are posted on Brightspace with everything she talked about.
Elle est en tant que personne super mais le contenu du cours est long et répétitif... Seul le DGD est utile.
She's very funny and full of energy. She can make a 7-10 fun. Very easy, I showed up to very few lectures and still passed with an A+
Very boring lectures, and she gets upset when no one is attending class. Might want to write down what she said in class because you need to cite her in your essays.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Good teacher and fun class. Tough final. Super nice lady.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'So many papers']

rComments: You can tell she knows her subject well but has a hard time teaching it. Lectures are boring. Her mind seems to be going faster than she can talk so her ideas are a little all over. Will randomly take attendance.
shes boring , lectures are boring, easy A, she knows no one goes to her lectures so she takes attendance every once in a while

She's a very fun and entertaining prof! I would definitely take her again! The class is a survey of francophone Canadian literature so it might be a bit boring at times if you're not totally interested in the subject. However, she tries to make her lectures as light as possible and is a very caring prof.

Class wasn't terrible, but was so easy that I didn't need to show up in order to get good grades. Don't miss the DGDs. She makes you buy like 5 books, 3 of them you'll never open. If I were to do it again I'd split the cost of the Rytec book with someone (you only use it once) and only buy the 2 books needed for the final. Don't buy the others.

shes so boring , lectures are useless, easy class, easy A if youre good in french, DGDS are far more important than any of her lectures; you could skip every single one and still pass with a good grade

The material of the class is boring and long, but she doesn't make it as bad. Her lectures aren't hilarious for me, but they are humorous and make the class easier to bare through. She teaches clearly and passionately, too.

The class is extremely easy. If you are fluent in French, it is an easy "A". I found her lectures very dull and long, however. This might be because the class material was too easy for me. Lectures aren't a must, but DGD are mandatory. You can skip all lectures and go to DGD and pass with an A.
Très bonne prof... le cours en général était long mais je pense que c'était seulement la matière
Very good prof.
Very funny and generally pretty awesome. Made the class interesting somehow.
She explain very well the subject. Her explanations are clear most of the time, she has humour and she prepares her classes. I enjoyed her class and learn a lot. The TA Marie Galophe was also great.
Hilarious prof, really dynamic . Overall an easy class
Had Her for FRA 1710. Super easy class in which anyone with basic knowledge of french and grammar can get high marks. Overall, good prof

Very fun prof to have! Makes class very interesting and is the best when you go see her in her office for extra help. I enjoyed the 2 classes I had with her and would take ANY class given by her! Fair grader when it comes to tests, study what you learned and no surprises! Will tell you EXACTLY what to expect:)

Très bonne comme prof! Elle est un peu excentrique mais ça la rend très divertissante. Je l'ai apprécié dans mon cours d'intro! Mais... elle nous a dit elle-même que ses examens dans les cours de 2e et 3e année sont très, très durs.
